.TH "xcan_set_error_state" 9 "xcan_set_error_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xcan_set_error_state \- Set new CAN error state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" xcan_set_error_state
.BI "(struct net_device *ndev "  ","
.BI "enum can_state new_state "  ","
.BI "struct can_frame *cf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ndev" 12
Pointer to net_device structure
.IP "new_state" 12
The new CAN state to be set
.IP "cf" 12
Error frame to be populated or NULL
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set new CAN error state for the device, updating statistics and
populating the error frame if given.
